      "content": "i hear that, but doesn't the culture itself play a bigger role? i mean, when you look at these different groups, there's often just a natural tendency for certain tribes to be more aggressive or territorial with each other. like, is it even possible to have a stable democracy when the fundamental social makeup is built on these conflicting identities?",
